727349f-b.text:
Maspeth Ave., north side, east of 59th Place, showing in the foreground the Eolyer farmhouse which was taken down about April 1923, because it stood directly in the line of the proposed 60th Street. Beyond the house is a two story frame structure bearing No. 6007, being 50 ft. east of 60th Street. The Eoyler house of 1875 was owned by J. Divine 1850, Schwigert 1873, and Van Master
in 1891. This is a set of four views.
March 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
